SKENE OF wus'rukcousu AND RAMORE. 105

“Robert Skene of Ramore descended of a second brother of the Laird of Skene” records arms in the Lyon Register: “Gules three daggers argent pomelled and surmounted on the poynts with alse many woolt's heads couped or, all within a bordur inveehed of the second.” Crest: “ A birk-tree environed with certaine ears of oats all growing out of a mount proper.” Motto: “Sub montibusaltisss'

He was three times married, 1st, to a daughter of Rait of Halgreen, and, to Barbara, daughter of Williarn Forbes of Cotton, and relictos Gilbert Skene of Dyce‚ and 3rd, to a daughter of Robert Irvine of Culta

By his first wife he had an only daughter, Margaret Skene, who married James Hog of Blairiedryne, and brought the estate of Ramore into that family. ψ
